{"parse":{"title":"The J.R.R. Tolkien Lecture on Fantasy Literature","pageid":54340588,"revid":857348490,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>The J.R.R. Tolkien Lecture on Fantasy Literature</b> is a free public lecture delivered annually at <a href=\"/wiki/Pembroke_College,_Oxford_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pembroke College, Oxford University\">Pembroke College, Oxford University</a>.\n</p><p>The series was founded by Pembroke postgraduate students Will Badger and Gabriel Schenk in memory of <a href=\"/wiki/J.R.R._Tolkien\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"J.R.R. Tolkien\">J.R.R. Tolkien</a>, who was <a href=\"/wiki/Rawlinson_and_Bosworth_Professor_of_Anglo-Saxon\" title=\"Rawlinson and Bosworth Professor of Anglo-Saxon\">Rawlinson and Bosworth Professor of Anglo-Saxon</a> at Pembroke from 1925 until 1945. The aim of the series is to stimulate more serious study of fantasy literature at Oxford University and beyond. The lecture can be on any subject dealing with fantasy, science fiction, horror, or related speculative genres.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Pembroke College Middle Common Room announced the series in 2012,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and the first lecture was delivered on 18 January 2013 by fantasy writer <a href=\"/wiki/Kij_Johnson\" title=\"Kij Johnson\">Kij Johnson</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The latest lecture was given by <a href=\"/wiki/V._E._Schwab\" title=\"V. E. Schwab\">Victoria 'V.E.' Schwab</a> in 2018.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Science Fiction critic, writer, and publisher <a href=\"/wiki/Cheryl_Morgan\" title=\"Cheryl Morgan\">Cheryl Morgan</a> regularly blogs about the lecture series on her website.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Fantasy author <a href=\"/wiki/Juliet_E._McKenna\" title=\"Juliet E. McKenna\">Juliet E. McKenna</a> has also written about the series.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_J.R.R._Tolkien_Lecture_on_Fantasy_Literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Date</th>\n<th>Lecturer</th>\n<th>Title\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>May 1, 2018</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/V._E._Schwab\" title=\"V. E. Schwab\">Victoria 'V.E.' Schwab</a></td>\n<td><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://tolkienlecture.org/2018/05/02/video-for-victoria-v-e-schwabs-tolkien-lecture/\">In Search of Doors</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>April 27, 2017</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Susan_Cooper\" title=\"Susan Cooper\">Susan Cooper</a></td>\n<td><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://tolkienlecture.org/2017/04/30/susan-coopers-tolkien-lecture/\">A Catch of the Breath</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>May 26, 2016</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Terri_Windling\" title=\"Terri Windling\">Terri Windling</a></td>\n<td><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://tolkienlecture.org/2016/06/01/photographs-podcast-and-video-for-the-fourth-tolkien-lecture/\">Tolkien\u2019s Long Shadow: Reflections on Fantasy Literature in the Post-Tolkien Era</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>May 13, 2015</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Lev_Grossman\" title=\"Lev Grossman\">Lev Grossman</a></td>\n<td><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://tolkienlecture.org/2015/06/11/video-lev-grossman-fear-and-loathing-in-aslands-land/\">Fear and Loathing in Aslan\u2019s Land</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>May 2, 2014</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Adam_Roberts_(British_writer)\" title=\"Adam Roberts (British writer)\">Adam Roberts</a></td>\n<td><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://tolkienlecture.org/2014/05/14/adam-roberts-lecture-podcast-now-available/\">Tolkien and Women</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>January 18, 2013</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Kij_Johnson\" title=\"Kij Johnson\">Kij Johnson</a></td>\n<td><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://tolkienlecture.org/2013/02/08/pdf-version-of-the-first-plfl/\">Inaugural Pembroke Lecture on Fantasy Literature in Honour of J.R.R. Tolkien</a>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_J.R.R._Tolkien_Lecture_on_Fantasy_Literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://tolkienlecture.org/about-us/\">About Us</a>, The J.R.R. Tolkien Lecture on Fantasy Literature</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://tolkienlecture.org/2012/12/\">Announcing the First Annual Pembroke Lecture on Fantasy Literature in Honour of JRR Tolkien</a>, The J.R.R. Tolkien Lecture on Fantasy Literature, December 6, 2012. Retrieved 19 June 2017.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Matt Handley,\n <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://oxfordstudent.com/2013/01/10/pembroke-to-introduce-fantasy-lecture/\">Pembroke To Introduce Fantasy Lecture</a>, <i>The Oxford Student</i>, January 10, 2013. Retrieved 19 June 2017.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Matthew Reza, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.oxonianreview.org/wp/writing-the-fantastic/\">Writing the Fantastic</a>, <i>The Oxonian Review</i>, January 18, 2012. Retrieved June 19, 2017.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Louis Morris, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"https://www.pmb.ox.ac.uk/news/bestselling-author-ve-schwab-delivers-sixth-annual-jrr-tolkien-lecture-fantasy-literature\">[1]</a>, Pembroke College, Oxford, May 4, 2018. Retrieved 13 May 2018.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Cheryl Morgan, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.cheryl-morgan.com/?p=25448\">V.E. Schwab\u2019s Tolkien Lecture</a>, <i>Cheryl's Mewsings</i>, May 2, 2018. Retrieved May 13, 2018.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-tex